title: Iowa Firm Recalls Barbecue Sausage Products That May Be Undercooked
summary: WASHINGTON, Nov 13, 2012 –Pinnacle Foods Group LLC a Fort Madison, Iowa establishment, is recalling approximately 90,975 pounds of bourbon barbecue sausage products because they may have been underprocessed, the U.S. Department of Agriculture’s Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today. The products subject...
impacted_products: 5-oz. cans of “Armour Vienna Sausage Bourbon BBQ Flavored” (24 per case).
